        },
        {
            "_id": "4CT0cZYglQW0zFjC",
            "img": "systems/pf2e/icons/default-icons/action.svg",
            "name": "Vitriol",
            "sort": 900000,
            "system": {
                "actionType": {
                    "value": "action"
                },
                "actions": {
                    "value": 1
                },
                "category": "offensive",
                "description": {
                    "value": "<p>The hateful hodag vomits a stream of caustic black sludge at a single foe it can detect within 15 feet. The hodag and the target each gain a +1 circumstance bonus on all attack rolls made against each other until the hodag chooses a different target for its Vitriol. The target must attempt a @Check[will|dc:22] save, with the following effects. The hodag cannot use Vitriol again for [[/br 1d4 #rounds]]{1d4 rounds}.</p>\n<hr />\n<p><strong>Critical Success</strong> No effect.</p>\n<p><strong>Success</strong> The target's mind is clouded by feelings of rage and hate, causing it to be @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.conditionitems.Item.Off-Guard] against the hodag's next attack. It can't use actions with the concentrate trait unless they also have the rage trait.</p>\n<p><strong>Failure</strong> As success, but the target is off-guard until the end of the hodag's next turn. While off-guard, it is unable to use actions with the concentrate trait unless they also have the rage trait.</p>\n<p><strong>Critical Failure</strong> As failure, but the target is off-guard until the hodag chooses a different target for its Vitriol.</p>"
                },
